<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE011FCBCFBF8" blockId="6.[151,839,1073,1099]" box="[151,839,1073,1099]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading id="D0D07F52FFC6FF99FF2BE011FCBCFBF8" bold="true" box="[151,839,1073,1099]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFC6FF99FF2BE011FCBCFBF8" bold="true" box="[151,839,1073,1099]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Key to males of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFC6FF99FE31E011FDF5FBF8" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Walsingham" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[397,526,1073,1099]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Episimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submicans">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFC6FF99FE31E011FDF5FBF8" bold="true" box="[397,526,1073,1099]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">submicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group based on genitalia
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D9BB5FFC6FF99FF2BE05CFA67F952" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="key">
<keyStep id="30D3D09BFFC6FF99FF2BE05CFA60FB48" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE05CFA60FB05" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE05CFA60FB05" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
1. Setae from basal one-third of valva dramatically asymmetrical from left to right side, with extremely elongate setae on left valva (greater than half the length of valva), and fewer, much shorter setae on right valva (
<figureCitation id="131CD4BBFFC6FF99FB69E0BFFAAAFB05" box="[1237,1361,1183,1206]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="38.[151,269,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[188,1395,178,1971]" captionTargetId="figure-56@38.[188,1397,134,1999]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Male genitalia of Megalota; valva spread, phallus removed. 25. M. submicans, image of USNM slide 85,857; 26. M. synchysis, image of USNM slide 84,873; 27. M. peruviana, image of USNM slide 84,891." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307548/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs. 25-27</figureCitation>
) ...... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE0E2FA60FB48" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE0E2FA60FB48" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">- Setae from basal one-third of valva essentially symmetrical from left to right side, with setae less than one-half the length of valva .............................................................................................................................................................. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30D3D09BFFC6FF99FF2BE127FA67FAD7" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE127FA60FAAD" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" box="[151,1435,1287,1310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE127FA60FAAD" box="[151,1435,1287,1310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
2. Basal process of the valva&gt; 3 times as long as wide, narrowed distally (
<figureCitation id="131CD4BBFFC6FF99FC7BE127FBBCFAAD" box="[967,1095,1287,1310]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="38.[151,269,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[188,1395,178,1971]" captionTargetId="figure-56@38.[188,1397,134,1999]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Male genitalia of Megalota; valva spread, phallus removed. 25. M. submicans, image of USNM slide 85,857; 26. M. synchysis, image of USNM slide 84,873; 27. M. peruviana, image of USNM slide 84,891." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307548/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs. 26, 27</figureCitation>
) ............................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE10AFA67FAD7" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE10AFA67FAD7" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
- Basal process of the valva &lt;3 times as long as wide, more or less uniformly in width or slightly narrowed subbasally .................................................................................................................................................................... 1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFC6FF99FA97E16DFA67FAD7" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Walsingham" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[1323,1436,1357,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Episimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submicans">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFC6FF99FA97E16DFA67FAD7" box="[1323,1436,1357,1380]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">submicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30D3D09BFFC6FF99FF2BE14FFA67FA1A" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE14FFA67FA35" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" box="[151,1436,1391,1414]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE14FFA67FA35" box="[151,1436,1391,1414]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
3. Distal end of phallus with flattened flange (
<figureCitation id="131CD4BBFFC6FF99FD29E14FFD1FFA35" box="[661,740,1391,1414]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="38.[151,269,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[188,1395,178,1971]" captionTargetId="figure-56@38.[188,1397,134,1999]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Male genitalia of Megalota; valva spread, phallus removed. 25. M. submicans, image of USNM slide 85,857; 26. M. synchysis, image of USNM slide 84,873; 27. M. peruviana, image of USNM slide 84,891." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307548/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
), lacking thorns .........................................................3. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFC6FF99FA8CE14FFA67FA35" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" box="[1328,1436,1391,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFC6FF99FA8CE14FFA67FA35" box="[1328,1436,1391,1414]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE1B2FA67FA1A" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" box="[151,1436,1426,1449]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE1B2FA67FA1A" box="[151,1436,1426,1449]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
- Distal end of phallus without flattened flange, with one or two minute thorns (
<figureCitation id="131CD4BBFFC6FF99FBBBE1B2FBAEFA1A" box="[1031,1109,1426,1449]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–27" captionStartId="38.[151,269,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[188,1395,178,1971]" captionTargetId="figure-56@38.[188,1397,134,1999]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 25–27. Male genitalia of Megalota; valva spread, phallus removed. 25. M. submicans, image of USNM slide 85,857; 26. M. synchysis, image of USNM slide 84,873; 27. M. peruviana, image of USNM slide 84,891." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307548/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) ............................2. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFC6FF99FA8BE1B2FA67FA1A" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" box="[1335,1436,1426,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="synchysis">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFC6FF99FA8BE1B2FA67FA1A" box="[1335,1436,1426,1449]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">synchysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30D3D09BFFC6FF99FF2BE194FA60FA5D" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE194FA67FA7F" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" box="[151,1436,1460,1484]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE194FA67FA7F" box="[151,1436,1460,1484]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
4. Uncus with anterior edge straight; posterior edge of tegumen with deep lateral notch (
<figureCitation id="131CD4BBFFC6FF99FBE4E194FB5DFA78" box="[1112,1190,1460,1483]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–30" captionStartId="39.[151,269,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,178,1971]" captionTargetId="figure-52@39.[189,1398,138,2003]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 28–30. Male genitalia of Megalota; valva spread, phallus removed. 28. M. aquilonaris, image of USNM slide 124,098; 29. M. vulgaris, image of USNM slide 124,184; 30. M. cacaulana, image of USNM slide 85,871." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307550" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307550/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
).............. 6. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFC6FF99FA91E195FA67FA7F" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" box="[1325,1436,1461,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cacaulana">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFC6FF99FA91E195FA67FA7F" box="[1325,1436,1461,1484]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">cacaulana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE1F7FA60FA5D" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" box="[151,1435,1495,1518]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE1F7FA60FA5D" box="[151,1435,1495,1518]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">- Uncus with anterior edge rounded; posterior edge of tegumen with shallow lateral notch ......................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30D3D09BFFC6FF99FF2BE1DAFA60F9CA" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE1DAFA60F987" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE1DAFA60F987" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
5. Socius in the form of a conspicuous, rounded, pendant lobe; subbasal patch of setae a dense, compact cluster (
<figureCitation id="131CD4BBFFC6FF99FACDE1DAFF19F980" captionStart="FIGURES 31–33" captionStartId="40.[151,269,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,178,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-56@40.[192,1398,138,2000]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 31–33. Male genitalia of Megalota; valva spread, phallus removed. 31. M. macrosocia, image of USNM slide 124,139; 32. M. ochreoapex, image of USNM slide 85,863; 33. M. spinulosa, image of USNM slide 84,895." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307552/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
)............................................................................................................................................................7. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFC6FF99FA9CE23DFA60F987" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" box="[1312,1435,1565,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrosocia">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFC6FF99FA9CE23DFA60F987" box="[1312,1435,1565,1588]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">macrosocia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE21FFA60F9CA" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE21FFA60F9CA" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">- Socii short, membranous, reduced to a patch of fine hairlike bristles; subbasal patch of setae more sparse, not forming a compact cluster..................................................................................................................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30D3D09BFFC6FF99FF2BE2A4FA67F952" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE2A4FA60F92F" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" box="[151,1435,1668,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE2A4FA60F92F" box="[151,1435,1668,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
6. Distal setae of incurved process from mid-valva as long as process, projecting ventrally (
<figureCitation id="131CD4BBFFC6FF99FBC6E2A4FB3CF928" box="[1146,1223,1668,1691]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–30" captionStartId="39.[151,269,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,178,1971]" captionTargetId="figure-52@39.[189,1398,138,2003]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 28–30. Male genitalia of Megalota; valva spread, phallus removed. 28. M. aquilonaris, image of USNM slide 124,098; 29. M. vulgaris, image of USNM slide 124,184; 30. M. cacaulana, image of USNM slide 85,871." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307550" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307550/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
)............. 5. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFC6FF99FAF8E2A5FA60F92F" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" box="[1348,1435,1669,1692]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFC6FF99FAF8E2A5FA60F92F" box="[1348,1435,1669,1692]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98C83EFFC6FF99FF2BE287FA67F952" blockId="6.[151,1436,1148,1761]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="30D66B0BFFC6FF99FF2BE287FA67F952" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
- Distal setae of incurved process from mid-valva shorter than process, projecting outward-laterally (
<figureCitation id="131CD4BBFFC6FF99FB55E287FACCF90D" box="[1257,1335,1703,1726]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–30" captionStartId="39.[151,269,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,178,1971]" captionTargetId="figure-52@39.[189,1398,138,2003]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 28–30. Male genitalia of Megalota; valva spread, phallus removed. 28. M. aquilonaris, image of USNM slide 124,098; 29. M. vulgaris, image of USNM slide 124,184; 30. M. cacaulana, image of USNM slide 85,871." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307550" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307550/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) ............. ...................................................................................................................................................................4. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27B3BDFFC6FF99FA9DE2EAFA67F952" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" box="[1313,1436,1738,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aquilonaris">
<emphasis id="B953142CFFC6FF99FA9DE2EAFA67F952" box="[1313,1436,1738,1761]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">aquilonaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
